I"k<p>The <code>thingspeak</code> integrations makes Home Assistant communicate with the <a href="https://thingspeak.com/">ThingSpeak API</a>.
For now, it records exactly one entity at once, which is great for testing purposes. For long-time storage you should rely on the <a href="/integrations/influxdb/">InfluxDB component</a>.</p>
<h2>Configuration</h2>
<p>You will have to create a <a href="https://thingspeak.com/channels/new">new channel</a> on ThingSpeak and grab your Write API Key from the “API Keys” tab of the channel you want to use.</p>
<p>To setup the ThingSpeak integration in your installation, add the following to your <code>configuration.yaml</code> file:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Example configuration.yaml entry
thingspeak:
  api_key: MY_API_KEY
  id: 1337
  whitelist: sensor.yr_temperature
</code></pre>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='api_key' href='#api_key'></a> api_key</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>Your ThingSpeak Channel Write API key.</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='id' href='#id'></a> id</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='integer'>integer</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>The ID of your desired ThingSpeak channel.</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='whitelist' href='#whitelist'></a> whitelist</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>The name of the entity whose states should be sent to the channel.</p>
</span></p></dd></dl>
</div>
